there was a king, who had three sons. He loved them all very much, but especially the youngest. He made a great feast, to which he invited not only his sons, but also the wise men of the land, that they might make merry with him. When the feast was over, the king gave to each of his sons a sealed box, in which was a tiny mouse. He said to them, "I am about to die, and you shall keep the kingdom after me.
